description: Known as the Great Pegasus Cluster or M15. It is one of the oldest globular clusters estimated at 12 billion years old and contains around 100,000 stars. The cluster is located in the constellation Pegasus about 33,000 light years away. The image is composed of 170 stacked frames exposed at 30 seconds each.
